The paper deals with the decidability of language emptiness for a subclass of parametric timed automata. This involves the study of formal languages and automata theory, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper involves the use of parameters and clocks, which are common in the study of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also deals with the decidability of language emptiness, which is a fundamental problem in formal language theory (cs.FL). The study of timed automata and their decidability is also related to the field of dynamical systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the study of continuous-time models, which is related to the field of control theory (cs.CC).
